ZH: 如果你的销售额超出了目标，你将获得额外的提成。
EN: If you exceed your sales target, you will receive an additional commission.

ZH: 她每卖出一辆汽车，就能得到一定比例的提成。
EN: She gets a certain percentage of commission for every car she sells.

ZH: 他很努力地工作，争取获得更多的提成。
EN: He works hard to earn more commission.

ZH: 他们的提成制度非常激励销售团队。
EN: Their commission system is highly motivating for the sales team.

ZH: 提成是根据销售额来计算的。
EN: Commission is calculated based on the sales amount.

ZH: 这个职位有提成制度，鼓励员工多做业务。
EN: This position has a commission system to encourage employees to generate more business.

ZH: 每个销售人员都有一个提成目标。
EN: Each salesperson has a commission target.

ZH: 我期待着我的提成能够超过上个月的。
EN: I'm looking forward to my commission exceeding last month's.

ZH: 这个项目获得的提成将会平分给所有参与其中的员工。
EN: The commission earned from this project will be evenly divided among all the employees involved.

ZH: 他们设立了一个提成计划，以鼓励团队合作。
EN: They have established a commission plan to encourage teamwork.

ZH: 她的提成数额会根据她的销售业绩而有所不同。
EN: The amount of her commission will vary depending on her sales performance.

ZH: 公司决定调整提成比例，以激励员工更加努力地工作。
EN: The company decided to adjust the commission rate to motivate employees to work harder.

ZH: 我们的经理通过提成奖励表现出色的员工。
EN: Our manager rewards outstanding employees with commission incentives.

ZH: 他的提成与他的销售业绩直接相关。
EN: His commission is directly linked to his sales performance.

ZH: 他的提成是他工资的一部分。
EN: His commission is part of his salary.

ZH: 售后服务也会对提成产生影响。
EN: After-sales service also has an impact on commission.

ZH: 销售团队的提成由销售额决定。
EN: The commission of the sales team is determined by the sales amount.

ZH: 他的提成从本月的销售利润中计算。
EN: His commission is calculated from this month's sales profits.

ZH: 你的提成将会在下个月支付。
EN: Your commission will be paid next month.

ZH: 一些公司提供额外的提成奖励给最佳销售员工。
EN: Some companies provide extra commission incentives for their top salespeople.
